1
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:03,920
I just replaced your toothbrush.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,800
Why are you asking for a new one again?

3
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:10,440
The old one is worn out,
so I ordered a new one.

4
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,160
Warat?

5
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,600
Don't let him out of your sight.

6
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:26,000
<i>Follow him at all times,</i>
<i>no matter what he's doing or where he is.</i>

7
00:00:26,520 --> 00:00:28,240
<i>The DNA lab vehicle?</i>

8
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:29,960
Do whatever it takes.

9
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:32,520
<i>Get the case to the police</i>
<i>as soon as possible</i>

10
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,760
<i>and swap in the new evidence.</i>

11
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,960
Are you sure you want to come with me?

12
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,320
I don't even know

13
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,520
where I'm going yet.

14
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,320
Seeing you like this,

15
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,840
do you really think I'd let you go alone?

16
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,120
I'm just not ready to face anyone yet.

17
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,839
Then just keep driving.

18
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,680
I'm not even sure

19
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:28,320
if this might be the last time
I get to be alone with you.

20
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:38,480
Are you really going to do
what Grandma said?

21
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:49,560
If I already had the answer for sure,

22
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,840
I wouldn't be here with you.

23
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,720
That's why I told Mr. Supol

24
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,800
I wanted to talk to you first.

25
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:04,200
My grandma is afraid
I'll get caught in the crossfire…

26
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:09,040
because you're the target
of the attackers.

27
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:12,520
That's ridiculous.

28
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,960
Even though she knows we're together,

29
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,600
she still dares to use millions…

30
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,720
to separate us.

31
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,520
Like you said,

32
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:38,280
Mr. Supol and Grandma
are just playing along with us.

33
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,920
They've never believed
we're really together.

34
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,800
Drive.

35
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:02,080
Are you going to the Hua Hin branch?

36
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:19,040
See, Anong?
My leg is really getting better.

37
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:22,840
It is.

38
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,680
You're starting to move it on your own.

39
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:30,440
Not really.
I still have to support it with my hands.

40
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,640
I think

41
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:38,320
I should ask the doctor
to adjust your medication.

42
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:41,520
Oh no, no need.
I'd feel bad bothering him.

43
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:43,880
By the way, Anong,

44
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:50,200
that physical therapy center
is really good.

45
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:52,800
Skilled doctors, modern equipment.

46
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:56,160
I think you should get checked too.

47
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,560
Anong,

48
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,640
are you even listening?

49
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:11,080
I am. I was just thinking
I should look into it.

50
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:14,400
- But you should take your medicine first.
- Mm.

51
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:17,520
It's still warm, easy to take.

52
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,320
No, I don't think so.

53
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,000
The doctor said

54
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:24,720
treatments should be individualized,
not mixed together.

55
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,040
I see.

56
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:35,640
By the way, Sin said
Warat came to search the house.

57
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,800
Did he tell you about it?

58
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:41,680
He did, but I didn't pay much attention.

59
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:43,960
Not surprising.

60
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,200
His woman
was coughing up blood in this house.

61
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,600
Kluay…

62
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,800
I knew you'd know about this.

63
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,880
Why?

64
00:07:57,960 --> 00:08:00,960
Does Mr. Warat suspect
we harmed his woman,

65
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,760
so he came to search our house?

66
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:03,680
Mm.

67
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,360
I'm not entirely sure.

68
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:10,000
But Warat has started
to suspect something.

69
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,960
I think we need to hurry.

70
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:16,880
Have you talked to Sin yet
about what I emphasized?

71
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:19,040
Yes.

72
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:23,400
Sin said he'll make sure Warat
inherits everything

73
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:27,480
and becomes chairman of Vanich
as soon as possible.

74
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:29,520
Good.

75
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,040
Remind Jirasin

76
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:35,400
how enormous the shares are
for both him and you.

77
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:38,120
Don't waste time arguing with me.

78
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:41,200
Put that time to better use.

79
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:43,799
Yes.

80
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,040
And not just Sin,

81
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,920
you too.

82
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:56,040
For now,

83
00:08:56,720 --> 00:09:00,640
stay quiet. Don't cause trouble.

84
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:03,200
More problems will follow.

85
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,560
Just because I'm not saying anything

86
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:10,200
doesn't mean I don't know
what's going on, Anong.

87
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,200
Ugh.

88
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,480
I'm hungry. Let's go get something to eat.

89
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:34,640
Earlier, you said this might be
the last time we're together.

90
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,400
I won't let that happen.

91
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,440
Let's go.

92
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,720
Why aren't you eating? Don't like burgers?

93
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:09,600
No.

94
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,320
I…

95
00:10:12,680 --> 00:10:13,800
Mr. Warat.

96
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:17,400
I don't want a single baht of that money.

97
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:23,160
But I understand why Grandma
would offer money to make me leave you.

98
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:26,880
Don't think about it too much.

99
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,400
Right now, I just want to

100
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:35,400
finish helping Ms. Ampha.

101
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:38,320
And then I'll leave without taking
anything from her.

102
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:41,280
No, Kluay, don't think like that.

103
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,600
Can I ask you something?

104
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:52,320
Why do rich people think
money can buy everything?

105
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,920
Why do they think

106
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,440
that everything I've done,
being here with you, is because of money?

107
00:10:57,520 --> 00:11:01,840
Or has Grandma only ever met people
who came for her money?

108
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:05,520
No one was sincere to her at all?

109
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,120
For me,

110
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:11,600
I think what we're doing
is too complicated.

111
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:15,720
And Grandma has the right to question

112
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:19,080
what you really want
by coming into my life

113
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:22,160
and getting involved in Ms. Ampha's case.

114
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:24,200
So she assumes

115
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,120
you want money

116
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:29,080
and offers it to you.

117
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,760
But don't overthink it.

118
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,760
You're you.

119
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:42,560
You're genuine, kind,

120
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:45,720
and always willing to help others.

121
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:47,880
Yes.

122
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:55,240
But you're lucky too.
At least you have Grandma.

123
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,000
You also have Mama Toi.

124
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:05,200
But you're still luckier.

125
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:08,360
At least you know who your parents are.

126
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,240
As for me,

127
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:14,800
I still don't even know
who my parents really are.

128
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:18,920
Were they criminals? Were they bad people?

129
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:20,960
Don't think about that.

130
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:25,720
Focus on today, on now.

131
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,080
Today, now?

132
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,080
Yes.

133
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:33,800
Focus on who you are right now,
what you're doing,

134
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,440
what you're thinking.

135
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:38,080
I think

136
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:43,680
being you is already more than enough.

137
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:48,320
Have you noticed?

138
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:52,120
Everyone around you,

139
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:55,760
you make them happy.

140
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,400
You give them smiles.

141
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,560
Som, Mama Toi,

142
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,720
and me too.

143
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,560
Being near you makes me smile,

144
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,680
makes me happy.

145
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,320
Thank you.

146
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,080
Alright.

147
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:16,800
You make me happy too.

148
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:18,320
- Really?
- Yeah.

149
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:56,160
It's nice to get to see
something more open like this.

150
00:14:00,920 --> 00:14:02,040
Back in the car,

151
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:05,800
you said Mr. Supol doesn't believe
that we're really dating, right?

152
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:08,120
Mm, yes.

153
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:12,240
And…

154
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:14,880
what do you think?

155
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:21,880
Well, I just want to help
Ms. Ampha like I promised,

156
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,600
and help you sort everything out first.

157
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,000
Thank you.

158
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:33,440
But it's probably beyond my place.

159
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:37,080
If Grandma really wants me gone,

160
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:39,040
there's not much I can do on my own.

161
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,880
We probably feel the same.

162
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,720
If it were just me alone,

163
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,640
well…

164
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:52,320
I wouldn't be able to do anything either.

165
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:54,920
Because all this time,

166
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:58,680
we've needed each other. I need you.

167
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:07,520
If they don't believe
we're really together…

168
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:13,560
Are you joking about this again?

169
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:16,760
Kluay.

170
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:22,000
I'm not joking.

171
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,080
You have to take responsibility.

172
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:30,440
Responsibility for what?

173
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:33,120
You kissed me twice.

174
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,040
You knew?

175
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,640
Of course.

176
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,160
At the hotel,

177
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,320
and at the hospital.

178
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,880
At the hotel,

179
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,920
I thought I was dreaming.

180
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,760
You were dreaming.

181
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:51,800
I wasn't.

182
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:00,040
Be my girlfriend.

183
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,040
Okay?

184
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:06,120
If you don't answer,

185
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,320
I'll take it as you not rejecting me.

186
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:10,760
Uh…

187
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,480
I…

188
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:32,760
Aw, Mr. Warat, are you crazy?

189
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:33,920
Kluay,

190
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:35,320
you're really beautiful.

191
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:37,800
Mr. Warat…

192
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,760
Who are you looking at?
There's no one there.

193
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,800
Ugh, I'm not talking to you anymore.

194
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:49,240
Kluay.

195
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:51,840
What makes you so sure I'm single?

196
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,360
Hey.

197
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,880
I know you are single.

198
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,320
Then reject me.

199
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:00,960
Just because I didn't reject you
doesn't mean I'm okay with it.

200
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,000
Kluay,

201
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:08,200
this time, when we hold hands,

202
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:12,240
it's not because of circumstances anymore.

203
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,640
We'll hold hands

204
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:17,240
to move forward together.

205
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,400
Let's be together.

206
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,560
Be my girlfriend.

207
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:26,160
Okay?

208
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:35,800
If you don't answer, I'll take it as yes.

209
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:38,880
Okay.

210
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:41,360
You're so cute.

211
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:17,480
Thank you, Det, for letting me come along.

212
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:20,200
I promise I won't bother you at all.

213
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:22,320
You focus on your work, okay?

214
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,280
Oh, and when you're done,

215
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:28,800
let's go find a romantic place
for dinner tonight.

216
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:31,600
You'll go swim
and then head to the spa, right?

217
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:32,600
Yes.

218
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:35,600
Okay, I'll go work then.

219
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,520
Sure.

220
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:41,040
No, Mr. Warat.

221
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,440
Det, look at the camera.

222
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,600
Oh.

223
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,440
I forgot you were in a hurry.

224
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:51,840
You dragged me down to the beach
on purpose, didn't you?

225
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:52,920
Hey.

226
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:56,080
Det, what's wrong? What's wrong?

227
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,720
Mr. Warat, stop.

228
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,080
Mr. Warat!

229
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,280
Hurry.

230
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,000
Those two…

231
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:14,240
Whatever sweet things they want to do,
that's their business.

232
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:15,960
It has nothing to do with me.

233
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:18,640
Listen carefully.
I'll say this one last time.

234
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,440
I don't feel anything for Kluay anymore.

235
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:23,960
Anymore?

236
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:27,680
So you did have feelings before.

237
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:28,880
See?

238
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:32,280
You're just picking a fight with me.
Go back to Bangkok on your own.

239
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:34,440
I'm staying here tonight.

240
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:38,080
Det. Det!

241
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:46,320
Kluay.

242
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,600
This is very important.

243
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:56,640
Yes.

244
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:01,840
Excuse me, Mom.

245
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:05,080
The chairwoman
has an interview in the lounge.

246
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:07,120
Oh.

247
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,760
Right. I completely forgot.

248
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,120
Do you need something?

249
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:13,400
I brought the documents
Mr. Warat raised concerns about

250
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,840
for the chairman to review.

251
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:17,960
That's fine. I can wait until she returns.

252
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:20,160
I won't disturb you then.

253
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,200
Mm.

254
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,880
Uh, should we…?

255
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,560
You mean Mrs. Wanee
is going to open the will?

256
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:39,080
Yes. I saw it with my own eyes.

257
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:41,160
I'm so happy, Sin.

258
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,800
You did the right thing.

259
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:47,200
Just stay still
and don't fight with anyone,

260
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,520
okay?

261
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,360
I told you,
I don't have time to waste anymore.

262
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,240
Soon,

263
00:20:56,760 --> 00:21:00,480
the Vanich family will pay
for everything they've done to us.

264
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,080
And when that time comes,

265
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,880
I'll laugh right in their faces.

266
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:12,520
Come on, Sin. You must be tired.

267
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:16,280
Go take a shower and get changed first.

268
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:18,280
- Alright. Go.
- It's fine.

269
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:19,840
I'll stay and help you here first.

270
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,040
Oh, no need at all.

271
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:24,200
I'm almost done.
I just have to water this part.

272
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:26,920
Auntie…

273
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Why are you planting them? They smell bad.
I can smell it all the way to my room.

274
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:35,360
Never mind.
There's no point talking about it.

275
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:37,720
You already know.

276
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:40,920
Go on, take a shower.

277
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,640
I've prepared a lot

278
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:46,000
of your favorite dishes.

279
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,680
Go on.

280
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,760
Whoa, Auntie.

281
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:53,640
I think you look really beautiful today.

282
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:54,560
Really.

283
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:56,960
Why? Do you think
something's wrong with me?

284
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:59,560
No, nothing's wrong.
You just look really beautiful today.

285
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:02,440
Since we have good news,

286
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:04,240
let's go eat out tonight. Come on.

287
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:06,800
- Let's go.
- Wait, Sin. What's gotten into you lately?

288
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:10,040
You keep asking me to go out.
What's going on?

289
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:12,560
It's good you remember, because
you still haven't gone out with me.

290
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:13,760
Come on, let's go eat outside.

291
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,240
- Let's go.
- Aw, no.

292
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:17,080
Anong, prepare some snacks.

293
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,960
We'll have guests coming over.

294
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,160
Sure.

295
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,480
She can't do it. She's going out with me.

296
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,560
It's alright.

297
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:27,800
I'll prepare everything
to welcome your guests first.

298
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:29,960
Who's coming?

299
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:31,280
An investigator.

300
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:35,240
They're here to question us
about Captain Chada's death.

301
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,280
Anong.

302
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,440
Do you remember?

303
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:47,320
I asked you before whether
Captain Chada came to this house.

304
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:49,960
You said no.

305
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,240
But the GPS on his motorcycle

306
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:56,800
showed he came here to this house

307
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,680
before he rode off

308
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,480
and got into an accident and died.

309
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:06,640
That's very strange.

310
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:10,080
How could that even be possible?

311
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:12,720
Hm, now I kind of want to talk to them.

312
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:15,280
I'll go get ready.

313
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:21,320
The one who knows exactly what happened,

314
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:24,200
the whole situation, the truth,

315
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:27,360
is your aunt.

316
00:23:49,360 --> 00:23:50,360
What?

317
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,560
Hey, this is our first date.

318
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,680
You've been staring down the whole time.

319
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:57,600
Do you know that

320
00:23:57,680 --> 00:24:01,480
aside from work, I'm actually really shy?

321
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:05,080
- Really?
- Mm.

322
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:12,320
What?

323
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:16,440
Hey, just eat.

324
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:19,360
I'll give it back.

325
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,040
What?

326
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:28,360
Once all this mess is over,

327
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:33,480
do you want to go on a trip together?

328
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:36,040
Where do you want to go?

329
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,640
The mountains? The beach?

330
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:43,560
Or maybe abroad?

331
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:46,720
I'd love to,

332
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:52,120
but shouldn't we figure out
how to survive Grandma first?

333
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:55,400
When we get back to Bangkok,
who knows what we'll have to face.

334
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,040
We just need to clear up this mess.

335
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:00,640
That's it.

336
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:04,200
Oh, by the way, on the way back,

337
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:07,960
I'm thinking of stopping by
the Hua Hin branch.

338
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,160
Did something urgent come up?

339
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:13,320
It's just that government agencies

340
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:17,040
sometimes show up
for inspections without notice.

341
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:20,080
I think it's a bit suspicious.

342
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,440
Mm.

343
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:24,160
Then should we go now?

344
00:25:24,240 --> 00:25:25,640
- Not yet.
- Oh?

345
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:31,280
This is our first date. Eat first.

346
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:35,680
We can eat in the car. Go do your work.

347
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,080
What's wrong with you?

348
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:40,840
Are you shy?

349
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:44,080
Don't look at me. Just eat. Hurry.

350
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,000
I'll go grab my laptop
from the car for a second.

351
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:48,400
Go ahead.

352
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:52,200
- Can I get a kiss on the cheek?
- No.

353
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:55,760
Hey. There are people around.

354
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,120
Hey.

355
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,800
- Excuse me, could I get the check?
- Of course.

356
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:16,800
Kluay.

357
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:21,080
Ameena?

358
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:26,360
Please wait a moment.

359
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:28,840
My husband, Mr. Rut,

360
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:30,000
is on a call.

361
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:31,600
That's fine, thank you.

362
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:34,440
In that case, shall we
speak with her first?

363
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:37,320
I'm happy to cooperate.

364
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,640
Then I'll begin.

365
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:43,520
On July 8th, around 4 p.m.,

366
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:47,000
did you meet or speak with Captain Chada?

367
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:48,960
No.

368
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:49,880
Well…

369
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:52,840
we may have spoken before that.

370
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:55,720
Could you briefly explain?

371
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:58,680
Captain Chada and my husband

372
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:00,480
were close friends.

373
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:04,400
Sometimes he would stop by to visit.

374
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:07,280
And occasionally we'd run into each other

375
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:09,440
at the market and such.

376
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:13,440
Then could you take a look at this photo?

377
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,120
It's from the motorcycle camera
of the captain,

378
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,600
taken in front of this house.

379
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,200
Mr. Warat.

380
00:27:33,480 --> 00:27:35,880
Oh? How did you get here?

381
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:38,560
Don't joke around. Where's Kluay?

382
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:44,480
You're asking about a girlfriend
of someone who clearly doesn't like you?

383
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:45,600
Is that how it works?

384
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,800
No need to be so aggressive.

385
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:50,120
I already believe
you and Kluay are together.

386
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:53,360
I just want to clear things up on my end,
what's been bothering me about Kluay.

387
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,720
Kluay and I
have been friends for a long time.

388
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,560
I don't want to lose that friendship.

389
00:27:57,640 --> 00:28:00,160
Oh. It's fine.

390
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:03,000
Kluay doesn't care
about petty things. Trust me.

391
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,080
I can answer for her.

392
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:06,120
You don't have the right
to look down on people like that.

393
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:07,600
Why not?

394
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:10,600
If someone
makes my girlfriend's life miserable,

395
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:13,760
ruins it again and again,

396
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:16,120
don't I have the right to protect her?

397
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:19,320
What was Kluay thinking,
choosing someone like you?

398
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:22,080
Looks like I'll have a long talk with her.

399
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:25,440
You can try.

400
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,320
Let's see if you can even
get close to my girlfriend.

401
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:40,680
Alright, I'll go back to work.

402
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:43,120
Yes, I'll be there.

403
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:58,920
- Kluay.
- Mm?

404
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:03,080
When Det and I kept our distance from you,

405
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:07,040
everything felt normal, right?

406
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,560
Mm.

407
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:12,960
So I thought
I wouldn't pick a fight with you anymore.

408
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,520
But do you know

409
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:20,640
everything I tried to do

410
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:25,400
has completely fallen apart?

411
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:29,400
Hey, calm down.

412
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:33,000
Sometimes people just run into each other.

413
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:35,600
If Det calms down, he'll understand.

414
00:29:35,680 --> 00:29:37,160
No way.

415
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:44,760
He'll think I planned everything,

416
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:47,120
that I made him run into you and Warat.

417
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,920
Whoa. That's crazy.

418
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:52,520
He wouldn't think like that.

419
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:54,960
Do you want me to talk to him?

420
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,080
No.

421
00:29:57,560 --> 00:30:01,120
If you tell him,
and he finds out I'm here…

422
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,240
Do you know

423
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:04,760
he already told me to go back to Bangkok?

424
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:07,240
But I'm still here.

425
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:11,080
It's okay, Ameena.

426
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:12,320
- Hey.
- Hm?

427
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:14,000
Can I get another drink?

428
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:15,400
- Hey, that's enough.
- Another one.

429
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:18,000
- You're already drunk.
- I'm not drunk.

430
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,840
I'm not drunk. Who's drunk?

431
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:23,360
- Here it is.
- I'm not drunk.

432
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:25,920
- You ordered more?
- Thank you.

433
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:26,880
So refreshing.

434
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:28,760
That's enough.

435
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:31,520
- No.
- That's enough.

436
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,080
- I want to drink.
- What happened?

437
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:34,440
Uh.

438
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:36,600
I don't know.

439
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:37,920
- Ameena.
- Look.

440
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:40,240
I didn't come here to cause trouble.

441
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:45,000
Today, I came with good intentions.

442
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:47,480
Really good ones.

443
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:51,240
Can I have just one more glass?

444
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,640
- That's enough.
- Just one.

445
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:55,840
Please?

446
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,240
Well, Kluay.

447
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:07,520
Turns out it wasn't a government agency.

448
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,840
A scammer?

449
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:12,360
Yeah, the police
have already detained them.

450
00:31:12,880 --> 00:31:13,840
Oh.

451
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:16,120
Then you should go ahead.

452
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,960
But I should stay and look after her.

453
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:21,040
- You'll be okay?
- Yes.

454
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:23,960
- Okay.
- You’ve got this.

455
00:31:27,520 --> 00:31:28,640
You’ve got this, okay?

456
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,400
- Alright.
- You’ve got this.

457
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:47,120
So these photos,
are they really in front of your house?

458
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:53,240
I'm just confused about

459
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:56,600
how there are photos
of the front of my house.

460
00:31:56,680 --> 00:32:00,320
But we've already verified
that it is indeed this house.

461
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:02,360
The captain
parked his motorcycle right here

462
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:06,000
for almost half an hour before riding off.

463
00:32:06,080 --> 00:32:08,960
That means he may have been here

464
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,640
or somewhere nearby.

465
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:13,120
Are you sure you didn't see him at all?

466
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:17,480
Just tell them, Aunt Nong,
that you were at the hospital with me.

467
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,000
Hello.

468
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:30,960
I'm Ms. Anong's nephew.

469
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:33,720
When you're not at home,

470
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:36,960
do you have to remember everyone

471
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:38,200
who walks past your house?

472
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,200
Sin.

473
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:44,240
That's my nephew.

474
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:46,640
He likes to joke around like this.

475
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:49,440
But what he said is true.

476
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:52,240
That day, Sin wasn't feeling well,

477
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:55,840
so I stayed with him at the hospital.

478
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:57,920
So I might not have seen the captain.

479
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:07,040
After I came back from the hospital,
I was here the whole time.

480
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:11,560
If someone rang the doorbell,
I would've heard it.

481
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:13,840
I think I'll bring you

482
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:17,800
the CCTV footage
from the front of the house later.

483
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:21,920
That would be great.

484
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:25,320
I'm not sure

485
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:27,120
if it'll help, officer.

486
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:28,440
That would be helpful.

487
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:30,920
- Thank you for your cooperation.
- Oh.

488
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:32,400
My pleasure.

489
00:33:45,400 --> 00:33:49,200
<i>This is a custom-made piece,</i>
<i>not something sold</i>

490
00:33:49,280 --> 00:33:51,600
<i>in regular gold shops.</i>

491
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,160
It's not Thai gold.

492
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:55,000
It's made from melted Western gold.

493
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:04,360
Careful, don't let it
hit Warat's face, Waree.

494
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:05,440
I'm back, dear.

495
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,240
Oh.

496
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,800
- How is it?
- Look at this.

497
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,159
- Are you tired?
- Not at all.

498
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:12,560
Look, the kids are having so much fun.

499
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:14,880
Thank you

500
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:17,199
for taking care of Warat.

501
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:20,600
So, where's the thing
I asked you to pick up?

502
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:22,239
Here.

503
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:27,600
And this too.

504
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:35,840
You even melted the gold you saved
to make this for your child…

505
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:39,520
<i>You can buy anklets anywhere.</i>

506
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:42,760
<i>Help Waree!</i>

507
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,760
Am I dreaming?

508
00:34:49,239 --> 00:34:51,880
Why is this so clear?

509
00:34:53,560 --> 00:34:54,920
That man…

510
00:34:57,960 --> 00:34:59,200
Wichan?

511
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:03,040
Wichan?

512
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:20,560
Yes, it's me, Toi.

513
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:25,760
Sorry for calling so late.

514
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:30,200
I wanted to ask about the new project

515
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:34,120
of the foundation with the Vanich Group.

516
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:36,880
Yes.

517
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:39,760
I've changed my mind.

518
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:42,680
I'd like to propose
the Baan Saeng Wan Mai project

519
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:46,240
to Mrs. Wanee,
the chairwoman of Vanich Group.

520
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:56,320
I've brought her upstairs already.

521
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:57,840
Don't worry.

522
00:35:58,360 --> 00:36:01,360
Are you still at the police station?

523
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:05,320
<i>Don't worry. Mr. Arnon is here with me.</i>

524
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:08,800
Then you take care of your business first.

525
00:36:08,880 --> 00:36:10,840
Don't worry about me.
I can take care of myself.

526
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,360
<i>You should take care of yourself.</i>

527
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,640
<i>I'm worried about you,</i>

528
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:17,560
<i>leaving you like that. I miss you, Kluay.</i>

529
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:22,000
I miss you too.

530
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,200
Mr. Warat, I gotta go now.

531
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,120
Ugh.

532
00:36:30,040 --> 00:36:30,880
Let me wipe you down a bit.

533
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,000
That tickles.

534
00:36:33,080 --> 00:36:35,080
It'll make you feel better.

535
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:36,560
Then go take a shower.

536
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:37,880
No.

537
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:40,880
- No.
- Why did you drink so much? Drink water.

538
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,160
- Come on.
- No.

539
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:44,520
Can I have a pillow? My neck hurts.

540
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,760
You're so stubborn.

541
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:49,920
How many do you want?

542
00:36:50,440 --> 00:36:52,880
Just one.

543
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:00,040
Lift your head up.

544
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:01,640
Mm.

545
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:04,200
- Is that okay?
- Much better.

546
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:06,320
Drink some water,
so you won't have a hangover tomorrow.

547
00:37:06,880 --> 00:37:08,240
I'm not drinking anymore.

548
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,720
You drink it. I'm fine now.

549
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:13,800
I brought it for you
and you won't even drink it.

550
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:19,240
Lie down.

551
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:25,680
Taking care
of a drunk person is this tiring?

552
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,120
Was I ever this bad when I was drunk?

553
00:37:50,120 --> 00:37:51,360
Sleep well,

554
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:53,840
idiot.

555
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:12,240
NEXT EPISODE

556
00:38:12,320 --> 00:38:14,440
<i>You really don't believe that Ameena and I</i>

557
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:16,680
<i>didn't do anything?</i>

558
00:38:17,840 --> 00:38:20,360
<i>Do you think what you're doing is right?</i>

559
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:24,000
I think it's worthless,
completely meaningless.

560
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:29,760
Lately, Anong's behavior has been strange.

561
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,080
Actually,

562
00:38:31,160 --> 00:38:34,160
I think it's been strange
since Prae passed away.

563
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:36,200
I'm not staying here.

564
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:38,760
Don't think I can't see through you.

565
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:40,080
<i>I'm not sick.</i>

566
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:41,800
I'm not staying.

567
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:44,520
Aunt Nong, I'm trying to help you.

568
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:49,400
Do you even realize what you're saying?

569
00:41:14,040 --> 00:41:16,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
